        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 9:15PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 915 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over John Tanner State Park,
or near Carrollton, moving south at 5 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, up to penny sized hail and frequent
cloud to ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Carrollton, Bremen, Temple, Bowdon, Mount Zion, Waco, Abilene, John
Tanner State Park, Lowell, and Bowdon Junction.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
